    "verdict": "ok",
    "note": "Stage-8 (Fable) adjudication — full sweep of all 90 rows (structure: comparative intensifiers — much/a-lot vs a-bit/a-little/slightly before comparatives; (not) nearly as…as; fewer vs less). Verify: register CLEAN, then fixed answers 1 (gf.012 keyed only 6 of 9 valid small×big intensifier combos → added the missing 3), level-gloss 1 (to-inform carrier \"the new voting\" → \"the news\"), translation 2 (to-advise-against \"warnen\" + to-take-care \"sich hüten\" demoted to partial — loose synonyms). The structure is correctly taught: big-diff carriers take much/a-lot/far, small-diff take a-bit/a-little/slightly; double-comparative/wrong-position/very+comparative are distractors; fewer↔countable, less↔uncountable. ~100 audited grants — the g3 gate gates even ordinary adjectives/comparatives/nouns as untaught (the bank indexes multiword entries as phrases). tf.001/002 redundant full-sentence answers demoted (pipe-split fills kept); \"blue\" reworded out of an explainDe (ASCII-umlaut false positive on \"ue\"). 0 fix, 0 drop → approve."
